00:23:48.880 --> 00:23:54.240
this kind of tools will provide you different 
reference, technical reference, so you can

00:23:54.240 --> 00:23:58.960
have some reference from one and some reference 
for others. So you can create a really great

00:23:58.960 --> 00:24:06.800
strategy. Then based on the screen readers, one of 
the most common questions that I have when I work

00:24:06.800 --> 00:24:14.720
with different projects is what about the screen 
readers? They usually ask if there is the, the,

00:24:16.240 --> 00:24:22.560
like what is the most critical screen reader 
that I need to to consider when we are creating?

00:24:22.560 --> 00:24:28.960
Well, I can say that it depends. It depends of 
the analytics of your site. For example, if the

00:24:28.960 --> 00:24:39.120
most visited browser is Chrome so you can need 
to try to design your strategy based on Chrome,

00:24:39.120 --> 00:24:44.400
but actually there is a combination of the 
screen readers that work, that works really

00:24:44.400 --> 00:24:52.720
good with Chrome and so on. So and now in on 
the screen I'm presented to you what is, sorry,

00:24:52.720 --> 00:24:58.160
what is the best combination that you can keep in 
mind when we are working with the screen readers?

00:24:58.160 --> 00:25:03.840
Actually you need to also consider if you are 
working with native applications, because it will

00:25:03.840 --> 00:25:10.640
be a little bit different, right, in terms of of 
of screen readers and the combination. It will

00:25:10.640 --> 00:25:16.240
be different in terms of gestures, also, because 
we need to use gestures and other additional tools

00:25:16.240 --> 00:25:23.680
that we can apply to improve the accessibility. 
And I will give you a gift. In this case,

00:25:24.640 --> 00:25:31.920
Include People with Disabilities. It's 
important just to don't take just

00:25:33.200 --> 00:25:41.120
for granted that the, all the checkpoints that you 
are doing at are enough. So this is a really

00:25:41.120 --> 00:25:49.200
great page that I want to provide you. The name 
of the page is Fable. So you will find people

00:25:49.200 --> 00:25:56.960
with disabilities as part of the board of this
company, so they can provide you in real in real

00:25:56.960 --> 00:26:05.840
time, what are the the most common defects of your 
page. We, if this page has specialized users in

00:26:05.840 --> 00:26:12.320
screen readers and magnification tools and also in 
code best practices, so they can provide you the

00:26:12.320 --> 00:26:20.480
tools you need in order to create a really great 
content. Then a couple of takeaways about this

00:26:20.480 --> 00:26:30.080
project is try to reshape your bias. Try to think 
differently, try to educate yourself and try to

00:26:30.080 --> 00:26:36.640
unlearn things because usually when we are working 
in the technical part we are superstructure,

00:26:36.640 --> 00:26:42.640
right. And we usually try to follow rules, 
but in this case we need to think differently.

00:26:42.640 --> 00:26:49.520
We need to just think in ways that that are not 
common when we are talking about accessibility.

00:26:50.080 --> 00:26:56.160
So that's important to reshape their 
bias. Also always think in your users.

00:26:57.360 --> 00:27:06.880
There, there is no more important to an honest 
feedback from your, for from your users, so try to

00:27:07.920 --> 00:27:10.960
keep in mind the user experience. What will be

00:27:12.560 --> 00:27:18.000
the experience of an screen reader user. So you 
can connect with different companies depending

00:27:18.000 --> 00:27:26.400
of the state you are, or depending of the 
country you are, there are specific like

00:27:27.200 --> 00:27:34.480
companies or services that you can send your link 
and those persons with disabilities can help you

00:27:34.480 --> 00:27:39.440
how to validate, what is the current experience 
from the from them in their site, so they can

00:27:39.440 --> 00:27:45.200
give you really real and honest feedback about 
your site so please keep in mind that option.

00:27:45.760 --> 00:27:52.880
And also, it's important to ask for expert 
advice. Why? Because sometimes when we start

00:27:52.880 --> 00:28:00.560
creating the accessibility process we, 
the learning curve is really long okay,

00:28:00.560 --> 00:28:06.160
because we need to understand what will be the 
success criteria that we need to cover in terms of

00:28:06.160 --> 00:28:12.800
of of the development code, what will be well, 
when will be enough to have the successful

00:28:12.800 --> 00:28:19.600
